abstract:
For any fixed $
u\ge 0, \delta\in \mathbb R$ and $x>0$, we investigate the
positive zeros of the derivatives $j'_{
u,\delta}(x)$ and
$y'_{
u,\delta}(x)$, where  egin{equation*}
j_{
u,\delta}(x)=x^{-\delta}J_{
u}(x)\quad	ext{and} \quad
y_{
u,\delta}(x)=x^{-\delta}Y_{
u}(x). \end{equation*} We derive asymptotic
expansions for their $k$-th positive zeros as $kightarrow \infty$.
